abstract: Cyprus police on Thursday arrested three employees of a high-tech surveillance equipment company owned by an Israeli former intelligence officer amid a probe of the firm's business activities.
snippet: Cyprus police on Thursday arrested three employees of a high-tech surveillance equipment company owned by an Israeli former intelligence officer amid a probe of the firm's business activities.
lead_paragraph: NICOSIA, Cyprus — Cyprus police on Thursday arrested three employees of a high-tech surveillance equipment company owned by an Israeli former intelligence officer amid a probe of the firm's business activities.
headline_main: Cyprus Police Arrest 3 Employees of Israeli-Owned Firm
headline_print_headline: Cyprus Police Arrest 3 Employees of Israeli-Owned Firm

abstract: A new British bill enabling the government to intervene in takeovers that threaten national security will include blocking the purchase of assets, such as intellectual property, as well as whole businesses.
snippet: A new British bill enabling the government to intervene in takeovers that threaten national security will include blocking the purchase of assets, such as intellectual property, as well as whole businesses.
lead_paragraph: LONDON — A new British bill enabling the government to intervene in takeovers that threaten national security will include blocking the purchase of assets, such as intellectual property, as well as whole businesses.
headline_main: UK Takeover Bill Could Help Block Sale of Assets to Protect Security
headline_print_headline: UK Takeover Bill Could Help Block Sale of Assets to Protect Security

abstract: Congress is giving states a last-minute infusion of federal funds to help boost election security with voting in early caucus and primary states slated to begin in February.
snippet: Congress is giving states a last-minute infusion of federal funds to help boost election security with voting in early caucus and primary states slated to begin in February.
lead_paragraph: Congress is giving states a last-minute infusion of federal funds to help boost election security with voting in early caucus and primary states slated to begin in February.
headline_main: More Election Security Funds Headed to States as 2020 Looms
headline_print_headline: More Election Security Funds Headed to States as 2020 Looms

abstract: Britain plans to balance the government's current budget, which excludes investment spending, within three years, Queen Elizabeth confirmed on Thursday as she outlined the plans of Prime Minister Boris Johnson's government.
snippet: Britain plans to balance the government's current budget, which excludes investment spending, within three years, Queen Elizabeth confirmed on Thursday as she outlined the plans of Prime Minister Boris Johnson's government.
lead_paragraph: LONDON — Britain plans to balance the government's current budget, which excludes investment spending, within three years, Queen Elizabeth confirmed on Thursday as she outlined the plans of Prime Minister Boris Johnson's government.
headline_main: UK Confirms Plan to Balance Current Budget Within Three Years
headline_print_headline: UK Confirms Plan to Balance Current Budget Within Three Years

abstract: Prime Minister Boris Johnson's government plans to introduce a 50% discount in business rates for Britain's small retailers to boost the country's struggling high streets and pledged a "fundamental review" of the whole system in the future.
snippet: Prime Minister Boris Johnson's government plans to introduce a 50% discount in business rates for Britain's small retailers to boost the country's struggling high streets and pledged a "fundamental review" of the whole system in the future.
lead_paragraph: LONDON — Prime Minister Boris Johnson's government plans to introduce a 50% discount in business rates for Britain's small retailers to boost the country's struggling high streets and pledged a "fundamental review" of the whole system in the future.
headline_main: Britain to Cut Some Business Rates, Conduct 'Fundamental Review'
headline_print_headline: Britain to Cut Some Business Rates, Conduct 'Fundamental Review'

abstract: European Union nations formally extended economic sanctions against Russia on Thursday by six months until July 31, the grouping of EU countries known as the European Council said on Thursday.
snippet: European Union nations formally extended economic sanctions against Russia on Thursday by six months until July 31, the grouping of EU countries known as the European Council said on Thursday.
lead_paragraph: BRUSSELS — European Union nations formally extended economic sanctions against Russia on Thursday by six months until July 31, the grouping of EU countries known as the European Council said on Thursday.
headline_main: EU Extends Economic Sanctions Against Russia for Six Months
headline_print_headline: EU Extends Economic Sanctions Against Russia for Six Months

abstract: The departures leave our critical infrastructure, elections, data and networks vulnerable.
snippet: The departures leave our critical infrastructure, elections, data and networks vulnerable.
lead_paragraph: At the end of 2019, with less than a year to go until the presidential election, the government official who has been leading efforts to secure voting systems in the United States will leave the Department of Homeland Security to join Google. The impending departure of Jeanette Manfra, the assistant director for cybersecurity at the department’s Cybersecurity and Infrastructure Security Agency, is a major loss for the federal government’s civilian cybersecurity efforts, and it comes at the end of a year that saw a series of departures by key cybersecurity personnel.
